From: Vinicius Costa Gomes <vinicius.gomes@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 28 Jun 2021 21:43:30 -0700
Subject: igc: Allow for Flex Filters to be installed
Patch-mainline: v5.15-rc1
Git-commit: 7991487ecb2d27f2293376411d576867a3d9640b
References: jsc#SLE-18377

Allows Flex Filters to be installed.

The previous restriction to the types of filters that can be installed
can now be lifted.

Signed-off-by: Vinicius Costa Gomes <vinicius.gomes@intel.com>
Tested-by: Dvora Fuxbrumer <dvorax.fuxbrumer@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tony Nguyen <anthony.l.nguyen@intel.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_ethtool.c |    6 ------
 1 file changed, 6 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_ethtool.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_ethtool.c
@@ -1300,12 +1300,6 @@ static int igc_ethtool_add_nfc_rule(stru
 		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 	}
 
-	if ((fsp->flow_type & FLOW_EXT) &&
-	    fsp->m_ext.vlan_tci != htons(VLAN_PRIO_MASK)) {
-		netdev_dbg(netdev, "VLAN mask not supported\n");
-		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
-	}
-
 	if (fsp->ring_cookie >= adapter->num_rx_queues) {
 		netdev_dbg(netdev, "Invalid action\n");
 		return -EINVAL;
